          class="lang-en-us">MKDoc 1.4. has been released. It features Unicode support, HTTP authentication and a brand new photo component.</dd>

        <dt xml:lang="en-gb" lang="en-gb" 
          class="lang-en-gb"><a href="http://mkdoc.com/news/booth-centre/" 
          hreflang="en-gb">Booth Centre website launched</a>
        </dt>
        <dd xml:lang="en-gb" lang="en-gb" 
          class="lang-en-gb">The Booth Centre, a charity for homeless people in Manchester, UK, launched their new website today, it runs MKDoc. </dd>

        <dt xml:lang="en-gb" lang="en-gb" 
          class="lang-en-gb"><a href="http://mkdoc.com/news/laptopchallenge/" 
          hreflang="en-gb">Laptop Challenge - the first multi-lingual MKDoc site</a>
        </dt>
        <dd xml:lang="en-gb" lang="en-gb" 
          class="lang-en-gb">Tomorrow the Laptops in the Community Challenge event will start and MKDoc will be used to author web content in multiple languages during the event.</dd>

        <dt xml:lang="en-gb" lang="en-gb" 
          class="lang-en-gb"><a href="http://mkdoc.com/news/mkdoc-in-japanese/" 
          hreflang="en-gb">MKDoc in Japanese</a>
        </dt>
        <dd xml:lang="en-gb" lang="en-gb" 
          class="lang-en-gb">The latest version of MKDoc now has full Unicode / UTF-8 support and a Japanese translation is underway.</dd>

        <dt xml:lang="en-gb" lang="en-gb" 
          class="lang-en-gb"><a href="http://mkdoc.com/news/mkdoc-in-punjabi/" 
          hreflang="en-gb">MKDoc in Punjabi</a>
